From: Xulei <B33228@freescale.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Dec 2010 17:18:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 152/233] I2C: Add support for 64bit system.

commit 0724d46417545aa3035d88fb8885dffe68817a8c upstream
correspond to vendor drop QorIQ-DPAA-SDK-V1-20110609-systembuilder.iso
0070-I2C-Add-support-for-64bit-system.patch

Currently I2C_MPC supports 32bit system only, then this
modification makes it support 32bit and 64bit system both.

Signed-off-by: Xulei <B33228@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Kumar Gala <kumar.gala@freescale.com>
---
 drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig b/drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig
index 9c6170c..3392f4b 100644
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig
@@ -422,7 +422,7 @@ config I2C_IXP2000
 
 config I2C_MPC
 	tristate "MPC107/824x/85xx/512x/52xx/83xx/86xx"
-	depends on PPC32
+	depends on PPC32 || PPC64
 	help
 	  If you say yes to this option, support will be included for the
 	  built-in I2C interface on the MPC107, Tsi107, MPC512x, MPC52xx,
